=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527817\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527817\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104geb1665703264511.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/geb1665703264511.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/geb1665703264511.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"geb1665703264511\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      AccessibleNameSeparator</h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Defines a string of characters that is used to identify parts of the MSAA accessible\n      name for Uniface interface objects. By default, a dot is used as a name separator.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"geb1665703264511__topic_d146039e1_d146040e1_d146041e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"geb1665703264511__p_d146042e1_d146043e1_d146044e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">AccessibleNameSeparator</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SeparatorString</var></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"geb1665703264511__section_w3331ab1b5b3_w3332ab1b5_w3333ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"geb1665703264511__table_d17828e1_d17829e1_d17830e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\".\"</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">File section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzj1665702614359.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzj1665702614359.html\" title=\"The [upi] section of the initialization file determines the appearance or behavior of many Universal Presentation Interface (UPI) objects under Microsoft Windows.\">[upi]</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"geb1665703264511__section_ywj_dvh_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d813664e105\">Arguments</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"geb1665703264511__table_d17831e1_d17832e1_d17833e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"geb1665703264511__table_d17831e1_d17832e1_d17833e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"geb1665703264511__table_d17831e1_d17832e1_d17833e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"geb1665703264511__table_d17831e1_d17832e1_d17833e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">SeparatorString</var></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"geb1665703264511__table_d17831e1_d17832e1_d17833e1__entry__2\">String of up to 16 ASCII or Unicode characters.\n                        If the string is longer, it is truncated to 16 characters. Letters are case\n                        sensitive. <p class=\"p\">If not specified, the default separator is a dot\n                              (<code class=\"ph codeph\">\".\"</code>)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"geb1665703264511__section_amn_gvh_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d813664e152\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">When queried by Microsoft Active Accessibility (MSAA) client, Uniface returns a unique\n            accessible name for the field widget. By default, this name includes dots for fully\n            qualified objects. For example:</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ORDERNR.ORDER.WAREHOUSE.21</code> identifies a field in the 21st occurrence of\n            an entity.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"geb1665703264511__p_d146060e1_d146061e1_d146062e1\">Some MSAA clients cannot accept the dot and create\n            their own accessibility name. For example, they may strip the dots, or add a sequence\n            number. The following unique Uniface names are all the same when the dot is stripped,\n            which makes it impossible to identify the Uniface object by its original name:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"geb1665703264511__ul_t1v_nvh_yvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"geb1665703264511__li_d50960e1_d50961e1_d50962e1\">ORDERNR.ORDER.WAREHOUSE.21 </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"geb1665703264511__li_d50963e1_d50964e1_d50965e1\">ORDERNR.ORDER.WAREHOUSE2.1 </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"geb1665703264511__li_d50966e1_d50967e1_d50968e1\">ORDERNR.ORDERWARE.HOUSE.21 </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"geb1665703264511__li_d50969e1_d50970e1_d50971e1\">ORDER.NRORDER.WAREHOUSE.21 </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">By setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">AccessibleNameSeparator</span> to a value that is accepted by the\n            MSAA client, it is easier to map the MSAA client's name for an object back to the actual\n            Uniface object.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"geb1665703264511__note_dxp_gwh_yvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Avoid using the underscore (_) or dollar sign ($)\n            as a separator, because the Uniface field name, entity name, and model name can contain\n            underscores, and entity names can also contain a dollar sign.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"geb1665703264511__section_d2h_vhw_cdc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d813664e197\">Example: <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">AccessibleNameSeparator</span></h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"geb1665703264511__p_d146069e1_d146070e1_d146071e1\">For example, the following setting:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"geb1665703264511__pre_ohy_gwh_yvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[upi]\nAccessibleNameSeparator = +</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"geb1665703264511__p_d146072e1_d146073e1_d146074e1\">results in Uniface MSAA-accessible names that look\n            like this:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"geb1665703264511__pre_phy_gwh_yvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">ORDERNR+ORDER+WAREHOUSE+21\nORDERNR+ORDER+WAREHOUSE+2+1\nORDERNR+ORDERWARE+HOUSE+21\nORDER+NRORDER+WAREHOUSE+21</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/abr1688541158363.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Accessibility</a><p>Uniface exposes the UI of generated Windows desktop applications to screen readers and automation tools for a number of widgets. By exposing the underlying infrastructure, screen readers and automated testing tools can target supported UI elements, and retrieve information regarding their name, value, and status. For these purposes, a mixture of two different technologies has been used - UI Automation and MSAA (Microsoft Active Accessibility).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527817\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527817\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "AccessibleNameSeparator Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 AccessibleNameSeparator Defines a string of characters that is used to identify parts of the MSAA accessible name for Uniface interface objects. By default, a dot is used as a name separator. AccessibleNameSeparator = SeparatorString Default value \".\" File section [upi] Arguments Value Description SeparatorString String of up to 16 ASCII or Unicode characters. If the string is longer, it is truncated to 16 characters. Letters are case sensitive. If not specified, the default separator is a dot ( \".\" ) Description When queried by Microsoft Active Accessibility (MSAA) client, Uniface returns a unique accessible name for the field widget. By default, this name includes dots for fully qualified objects. For example: ORDERNR.ORDER.WAREHOUSE.21 identifies a field in the 21st occurrence of an entity. Some MSAA clients cannot accept the dot and create their own accessibility name. For example, they may strip the dots, or add a sequence number. The following unique Uniface names are all the same when the dot is stripped, which makes it impossible to identify the Uniface object by its original name: ORDERNR.ORDER.WAREHOUSE.21 ORDERNR.ORDER.WAREHOUSE2.1 ORDERNR.ORDERWARE.HOUSE.21 ORDER.NRORDER.WAREHOUSE.21 By setting AccessibleNameSeparator to a value that is accepted by the MSAA client, it is easier to map the MSAA client's name for an object back to the actual Uniface object. Note: Avoid using the underscore (_) or dollar sign ($) as a separator, because the Uniface field name, entity name, and model name can contain underscores, and entity names can also contain a dollar sign. Example: AccessibleNameSeparator For example, the following setting: [upi] AccessibleNameSeparator = + Copy results in Uniface MSAA-accessible names that look like this: ORDERNR+ORDER+WAREHOUSE+21 ORDERNR+ORDER+WAREHOUSE+2+1 ORDERNR+ORDERWARE+HOUSE+21 ORDER+NRORDER+WAREHOUSE+21 Copy Related Links Accessibility Uniface exposes the UI of generated Windows desktop applications to screen readers and automation tools for a number of widgets. By exposing the underlying infrastructure, screen readers and automated testing tools can target supported UI elements, and retrieve information regarding their name, value, and status. For these purposes, a mixture of two different technologies has been used - UI Automation and MSAA (Microsoft Active Accessibility). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}